<p><b>Thomas Carlyle "Tom" Ford</b> (born August 27, 1961)<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> is an American <a href="Fashion_designer" title="Fashion designer" class="mw-redirect">fashion designer</a> and <a href="Film_director" title="Film director">film director</a>. He gained international fame for his turnaround of the <a href="Gucci" title="Gucci">Gucci</a> fashion house and the creation of the Tom Ford label before directing the <a href="Academy_Award" title="Academy Award">Oscar</a>-nominated film <i><a href="A_Single_Man" title="A Single Man">A Single Man</a></i>.</p>
